groups - command 

groups           -> for see groups
cat /etc/group   -> for see all groups in your system
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
groupadd - command

sudo groupadd group_name             -> for add group (group add in system datewise)
sudo gpasswd -a user_name group_name -> for add existing group to user
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
groupdel -command

sudo groupdel group_name             -> for delete group
sudo gpasswd -d user_name group_name -> for remove existing group to user
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
